import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='driving_hours_per_week', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['driving_hours_per_week'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['driving_hours_per_week'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of driving hours per week?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Driving Hours per Week')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='age', y='driving_hours_per_week', hue='age', palette='viridis', legend='full')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between age and driving hours per week?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Driving Hours per Week')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = data['distance'].astype(float)
    average_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(average_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {average_distance:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Distance Driven per Trip')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('Histogram of Distance Driven per Trip', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
